@NODE "How" "How"

3. How the game works.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   When the game first starts, you are looking at the playfield (on the left)
   and some self explaining stuff on the right.

   On top of the playfield you'll read "Press space when done"

   If you do not select a coin defaults to $1000

   By pressing F1 you select $   10,= which is shown on the bottom right.
      pressing F2 selects    $   20,=
      pressing F3 selects    $   50,=
      pressing F4 selects    $  100,=
      pressing F5 selects    $  250,=
      pressing F6 selects    $ 1000,=
      pressing F7 selects    $ 5000,=

   Use the mouse pointer, which is shaped as a hand of the croupier, by pointing his finger
   on the location of youre choise. Then press the left mouse button to drop the coin.
   The coin you selected with the F key is now shown on the location of youre choise.
   On the right side a message apears telling you what location you choose.
   You can bet about 40 coins per game (40 x $ 5000,= is more then most of us will spend in a casino)
   If you reached 40 coins a message apears" No more Bets please."

   Now on top of the playfield you will read "press Spacebar when done".
   By pressing the spacebar (or press Right and Left mouse button simultaniously-
   so you can play without keyboard-)
   the croupier will start the game and a number apears in the large vertical
   window. The croupier automaticaly pays or will shoot the wrong coins off the table.
   Press F10 for a new game.Or press RightMouseButton(RMB)
   Press 'U' for undo.
   Press 'S' if you don't want the SoundFX. In the 'Croupier window' a Sound on/off
   message apears shortly.
   Press 'C' to turn on/off coin in hand of croupier.
   Press 'Help' for....help!
   Press Esc to end Roulette '98
   Press 'V' to turn On/Off Voices exept rolling ball sound.
   Press 'D' to see NumberDataBase.
   By pressing key '2' you will save the amount of money you've got( Might be usefull when
   testing a system?)
   By pressing key '1' you will restore the previously saved amount of money.

   Hold left mouse button during startup to skip the intro.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "WhatWhy" "What `n' Why?"

2. What does it do and why ?
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Its a 90 % accurate French roulette game, based on the dutch version.
   I once went to a real casino to try my luck on the french roulette table with
   about £ 50. After only ten minutes (!!!!)I was broke and wend desilusioned back home.
   I then decided first to learn more about french roulette before I would try this again.
   I looked all over the place, in PD, commercial roulette games,
   but all I ever found were games in which you only could bet one coin. So I decided to create
   my own game. And here it is. Almost the real thing..

     IN A REAL CASINO, WITH £ 50, IT NOW TAKES 8 MINUTES TO GO BROKE .....
     SO KIDS, ONLY TRY THIS AT HOME.....


@ENDNODE

